                   1=Web driver--it is a writing advance test scripts(support all lang. and in lang. type)
--It ia a interface.
--Class vs Interface
---Class
        --Class is a encapsulation (collection) of data and method
--Interface--
        --it is, specifies a set of methods for implementation.
        --Defines only method signatures.
        --it is a package with various codes
        --some specific methods who works like class
        --In interface many class and methods also present(from abc import, abstractmethod)
--Abstraction is working  in interface where  many class and methods also present

on webdriver ----selenium code will write , without webdriver selenium code not possible
